The Comptroller General of the Nigerian Correctional Service, Jaâ€™afaru Ahmed is being honoured with a colourful pulling out parade at Headquarters of the Service in Abuja. He was born on 21st July 1959 and has been in the service since November 1989. The pulling out parade is being held at the parade ground of the Service at its headquarters in Abuja. Amongst dignitaries attending the parade are the Special Guest and Minister of Interior, Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola, the Minister of Justice and Attorney General of the Federation, Abubakar Malami (SAN) and the Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Interior, Dr Shuaib Belgore. Others are Representatives of Service Chiefs, the Comptroller General of Immigration, Muhammad Babadende and the Acting Commandant General of the NSCDC, Madu Kelechi. The CGC who bagged a degree in History from Ahmadu Bello University, Zaria in 1984 instituted various reforms in the service among which is the transformation of the Service from the Nigerian Prisons Service to the Nigerian Correctional Service with an enabling law. Ahmed who hails from Birni Kebbi, Kebbi State was appointed as CGC by President Muhammadu Buhari in 2016. He is married with three children.